    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.8.0-dev+211-g4c7462fdb\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux 5.17.5-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.25.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nI've git bisected to isolate the commit.\r\nI've also come to find this issue exists when using `packer.nvim`. `nvim -u NONE` doesn't cause this issue but I figured this might be a nvim issue as opposed to a packer issue.\r\n\r\n1. Get minimal_init.lua https://gist.github.com/jamestrew/7ba588b8c956db8c4829e6784b09f448\r\n2. Check out neovim 4c7462fd and build/install\r\n3. open nvim with `nvim -u minimal_init.lua`\r\n4. Close out of nvim with `:q`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nnvim promptly closes and can start typing in the terminal shell prompt almost immediately.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nTerminal hangs for approximately 2-3 secs and typing immediately after hitting `:q` results in something like this: \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/66286082/169629187-4152bfe8-2582-418f-b8db-505590cffa13.png)\r\n\r\nIt even shows a seg fault message occasionally after quitting.\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2022-05-21T01:39:36Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This only happens in Debug builds, which are used for, well, debugging. If you’re building from source to actually *use* Neovim, then you should set the `CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE` variable to Release or RelWithDebInfo when you run `make`.\r\n\r\nThe cause of the hang is that there are active libuv handles not being closed correctly, so Neovim is waiting for them to close before force-closing them. The “fix” is to find the offending plugins and fix it there.",
